5:00:29.000Z","msg":"At the invitation of WWE India, I went to watch a WWE match live, for the first time in my life, at an indoor stadium full of people screaming, laughing, jumping and guzzling tons of beers. I have been told by a thorough WWE fan that World Wrestling Entertainment (WWE) returned to Singapore after 8 years, hence it was a grand event. The best part was the audience, I saw an 80-year-old grandmother on a wheelchair cheering with her 6-year-old granddaughter with the same zeal. To top that, I obviously got VIP treatment &ndash; met Kane for a chokeslam, just kidding, it was a handshake and an autograph with a warm smile. King Barrett was also there.<br />\nSingapore stadium is a great venue with excellent facilities and the nearby food court has awesome variety of cuisine to offer. I though ended up having BK Charcoal flame grilled beef burger with whopper-size patty."},{"pid":"657d334dc4e196c9af4218ecdce5788550809b31","tid":2160402,"uid":364798,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-08-17T12:10:58.000Z","msg":"Vince收購左WCW之後就一直走下坡。<br />\n如果Vince 唔買WCW既話，宜家可能仲有好多人睇。"}]}